KATSINA – Alhaji Ado Liti ‘Yankwani, a former Bakori Local Government Council Vice Chairman in Katsina state has advised youths to desist from being used by any section of the society as tools of character assassination. ‘Yankwani gave the advice in an interview with newsmen in Katsina. He described the recent efforts by some misled youths in attacking the good corporate image of a Funtua based company in Katsina state, NAK General Merchant as evil, condemnable and unacceptable. Rangnick Explains Lingard Stay Linked To Greenwood Adebomehin Appointed As Substantive SGoF “NAK General Merchant as a good corporate citizen that is contributing to the economic and general welfare of the people of Funtua zone and Katsina state in general”. He wondered how some people with malice and hatred will designed the evil plot of misleading the youths to smear the name of such a good company. According to him, through the company’s investment initiatives a lot of youths have been gainfully employed, adding that, the company is also playing the active role of social responsibilities by assisting the needy and the indigent in society. He further described the acquisition of Katsina Steel Rolling Mill by NAK General Merchant as a major plus for Governor Aminu Bello Masari’s investment initiative drive for the development of the people and the state. He, therefore, called on youths and people of Katsina state to support and pray for the success of the company for the betterment of all.